description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join the Rehabilitation Team at Yeovil District Hospital NHS Foundation Trust. We are looking for a motivated individual who wants to support patients in reaching their rehabilitation potential by working alongside Physiotherapists and Occupational Therapists on the wards and in our reablement facilities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will ideally have previous experience working in a caring environment, with excellent communication skills and a real desire to enable patients achieve their personal goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits of working for us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working for a Trust voted 1st for Health and Well-being across the UK (NHS staff survey)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full NHS terms and conditions including extensive holidays, Agenda for Change pay with enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounts for local and national retailers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated well-being services for all employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working where possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Graham Ball - Physiotherapy Professional Service Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Graham.Ball@ydh.nhs.uk 01935 386030&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a part time role for 18.75 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
